[Bogomolov--Gieseker Inequality \cite{bogomolov_holomorphic_1979,gieseker_theorem_1979}]
Let $X$ be a smooth projective complex variety and $H$ an ample divisor on $X$. For any torsion-free $H$-slope-semistable sheaf $E$ on $X$, we have
\begin{equation*}
    \Delta(E) \cdot H^{\dim(X) - 2} \geq 0,
\end{equation*}
where the discriminant is defined by
\begin{equation*}
    \Delta(E) \coloneqq \ch{1}(E)^2 - 2\ch{0}(E)\ch{2}(E).
\end{equation*}.

